title: Netherlands Bankruptcies
description: Bankruptcies in Netherlands increased to 242 Companies in October from 180 Companies in September of 2022. Bankruptcies in Netherlands averaged 411.34 Companies from 1956 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 1185 Companies in May of 2013 and a record low of 72 Companies in February of 1956. In Netherlands, bankruptcies account for insolvent corporations who cannot repay their debts to creditors and carry on with their business. This page provides - Netherlands Bankruptcies - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Statistics Netherlands
